<h2 id="section-top">Palliative care</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1063">The Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent940cdc2ca0be471fbf75a35aa1b6c68a">
</div>
<p>A Palliative Care service is offered at both <strong>Chelsea</strong> and <strong>Sutton</strong> with a dedicated team consisting of Consultants, Clinical Nurse specialists, Matron and allied Health professionals such as Physiotherapists, Occupational therapists and dieticians.</p>
<p>The <strong>Chelsea</strong> site has a dedicated inpatient facility for management of symptoms and at <strong>Sutton</strong> this group of patients are managed on general wards with full support and responsibility of the Palliative Care team.</p>
<p>The majority of referrals to the Palliative Care team are from other clinical units within the hospital.</p>
<p>For further information on the service please see our <a href="http://www.royalmarsden.nhs.uk/diagnosis-treatment/patient-care/pages/palliative.aspx">website</a>.</p>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
